result.formatted_address: St Stephen's Ln, Sai Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Mitsuya

reviews.text:
This place is under new management. 
It is now more expensive and the portion sizes are smaller. Skip.

Fairly priced, like hkd 115 for a spring union tuna rice, hkd 138 for a stone grilled sirloin beef with rice. The stone grill is nice and seldom find similar thing in hk. They really serve on a rectangular hot stone. Add hkd 28 for a self serviced buffet salad bar with miso soup and small dishes octopus. Taste nice for the beef and the salad sauce. Lunch time all the main dish -$20.

Affordable sushi donburi lunch for around $78 to $148. Salad bar is $38 add on. Food quality is on par with the better sushi or Japanese teppanyaki places in Central. Kagoshima pork grilled rice was excellent.
Good food~
Tasty sushi!
